responses.question: Do you feel confident that things will work out for you?
responses.response_open: Rorschach: 「Confidence is an illusion, Nite Owl. In this cesspool of a world, hope is a luxury we cannot afford. But what I do have is certainty. Certainty that justice will be served. Whether it's through the system or by my own hands, the guilty will be punished. So no, I don't feel confident. I feel resolved. Resolved to fulfill my duty, no matter the cost.」

responses.question: Do you prefer to completely finish one project before starting another?
responses.response_open: Rorschach: 「None of you seem to understand. I'm not locked into the confines of your mundane notions of completion. You're locked into a limited mindset, unable to comprehend the depth of my dedication. I do not conform to your feeble concept of linear progress. My work is a continuous pursuit of justice, unyielding and unrelenting. Each project, each task, is but a piece of the greater puzzle I am assembling. There is no beginning or end, only the unending fight against the darkness that consumes this world.」

responses.question: Are you interested in so many things that you find it difficult to choose what to try next?
responses.response_open: Rorschach: 「Hmph. Choices. Always choices. I don't concern myself with such trivial matters. I have a singular purpose, a singular mission. To bring justice to those who deserve it. The guilty must be punished, and I am the instrument of their reckoning. None of you understand. I am not burdened by indecision. I am the one who decides.」
